# W6892-23B058: Acquisition of Traffic Lights for the Department of National Defence at Bagotville Airport
## Solicitation Number
WS4487780803
## Reference Number
WS4487780803-Doc4494117231
## Tender Status
Expired

The subject tender is a Request for Proposal (RFP) for the acquisition of traffic lights (lamps and light bulbs and lamp components) for the Department of National Defence (DND) at Bagotville Airport, located in Saguenay, Quebec. 

## Government Trade Agreements

This tender is open to bidders who are eligible under various government trade agreements, including:

* Canada-Ukraine Free Trade Agreement (CUFTA)
* Canada-Panama Free Trade Agreement (CPFTA)
* Comprehensive and Progressive Agreement for Trans-Pacific Partnership (CPTPP)
* Canada-Colombia Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA)
* Canada-European Union Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA)
* Canada-Korea Free Trade Agreement (CKFTA)
* Canada-Chile Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA)
* Canada-Honduras Free Trade Agreement
* Canada-Peru Free Trade Agreement (CPFTA)
* Canada-UK Trade Continuity Agreement (Canada-UK TCA)
* World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO GPA)
* Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA)

## Contracting Entity

The contracting entity is the Department of Public Works and Government Services (PSPC). The contract will be managed by the Minister's office and awarded based on Lowest Price selection criteria.

## Tender Submission Requirements

Bidders must submit their proposals electronically through the Ariba system. Bidders are responsible for the accuracy and completeness of their proposals. 

## Tender Closing Date
Tender closing date: 2024-06-27, 14:00:00 EST. No late submissions will be accepted.

## Contact Information

For further information, please contact Sonia Langis (SPAC/PSPC) at sonia.langis@tpsgc-pwgsc.gc.ca. 

## Notice URL

Please visit the following link to access the RFP document:

 https://discovery.ariba.com/rfx/19941273?extsite=MTk5NDEyNzNfQU4wMTQ4NDA1MDk5Mg==
